<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[99275]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The little mouse that swept the steps]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Theatre.</strong> A musical for all the family, an adaptation of a tale that has passed from generation to generation.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>&#8216;Once upon a time there was a mouse who used to sweep the steps of her house. She was a charming and pretty young mouse, but she was very absentminded and she didn&#8217;t like working very much&#8230;&#8217;. This is the beginning of the tale &#8220;The Little Mouse that Swept the Steps&#8221; which is on at the Teatre Gaudí Barcelona until 30 November.</p>
<p>It is a musical for all the family, been adapted by the Magatzem d’Ars theatre company. Their aim is to offer the audience a great show while bringing the world of music and dance to small children, using a story that is a real lesson in humility.</p>
